Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Combine mustard and celery seed in large bowl. Stir in macaroni; mix well. Add franks, undrained tomatoes, pickle, onion, celery and sport peppers, if desired; mix lightly. Spoon into 1-1/2-quart casserole dish; cover. Bake 30 minutes or until hot. Stir before serving.